HEADWORD: tui
<hw>⟦Eacute⟧`tui"</hw> <pr>(⟦asl⟧`tw⟦esl⟧")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F.]</ety> <def>A case for one or several small articles; esp., a
box in which scissors, tweezers, and other articles of toilet or of
daily use are carried.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

